            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="e1">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(etco) #iiv(erso) #142v" facs="001 003 145">Fols. ir(etco), iiv(erso), 142v</locus> blank </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a1">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, col. 1, upper</locus>
                    <q>“Praise and glory to God who helped me to finish in health and peace, amen,
                      in 1956 E.C., on the tenth of Säne”</q>
                    <date calendar="ethiopian" when="1964" when-custom="1958">1956 E.C., on the
                      tenth of Säne, (= April 18, 1964 C.E.) </date></desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a2">
                  <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, col. 1, lower (in blue)</locus> This
                    book belongs to Mara(?) Kǝbrat. The copyist is Ḥaraga Wayn of the land of Tǝgre.
                    The owner is willing this book to his <q>“learned child.”</q></desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a3">
                  <desc type="FoundationCharter">
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, column 2, bottom (black and red
                      ink)</locus> List of the family of the owner of the manuscript </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a4">
                  <desc type="ScribalNoteBequeathing">
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, column 3</locus> Will relating to a
                    list of other books he owns. These include books of Ziq, Four Gospels, Psalter,
                    Anqäṣ of Dǝggwa, Ṣoma Dǝggwa, Ziq [again], two copies of Horologium for the
                    Night Hours, and one book of Genesis. Written on Ṭǝqǝmt 10, 1970 E.C. </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="a5">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#141r" facs="143"> f. 141, col. 2</locus> “There was no rain in
                    1977 [E.C.] until the day of Raphael” [which is at the end of the year], <date calendar="ethiopian" when-custom="1977">1977 EC</date>
                  </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e2">
                  <desc> marginal notation throughout, some of which may be overlooked text </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e3">
                  <desc> Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24v #32v #44v #48r" facs="027 035 047 050">folss. 24v, 32v, 44v, 48r, </locus>, etc.); and lines of
                    text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12v #124r" facs="015 126">12v, 124r, </locus>);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is
                    to be inserted (<locus target="#131r" facs="133"> f. 131r, col. 1, line
                      8</locus>); text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#20r #22v" facs="022 025">20r, 22v</locus>) </desc>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 232 x 177 x 50 mm, four Coptic chain stitches
